Class Road

  • java.lang.Object
    • Road

  • public class Road
extends java.lang.Object
    Represents a settlement with a name, population, type and with connected roads.
    Version:
    1.0 (30th January 2015), 2.0 (15th February 2016)
    Author:

    • Constructor Detail

      • Road

        public Road(java.lang.String nm,
    Classification classifier,
    Settlement source,
    Settlement destination,
    double len)
        Constructor to build road between two settlements. This fulfills the class diagram constraint that every road must be connected to two settlements. We are not checking whether it's the same settlement, but that's okay: you drive out and arrive back again at the same place!
        Parameters:
        nm - The road name
        classifier - The class of road, e.g. 'A'
        source - The source settlement
        destination - The destination settlement (can be the same as the source!)
